<div class="banner d-flex" style= "background-image: url(<%= image_url("sniff.jpg") %>); height: calc(100vh - 120px); background-size: cover; background-position: bottom" >

  <div class="banner-content d-flex flex-column" style="background-color: #f4f3eb; height:100%; margin-left: 100px;">
    <div class="banner-content p-5 d-flex flex-column justify-content-end shadow-sm" style= "background-color: white; height: calc(100vh - 250px)">
      <div class="banner-content mb-3">
        <h1>CATCH</h1>
        <h4 class= "pb-2" style="border-bottom: solid 3px #f5593d;">THE TNR PLATFORM</h4>
        <h5><%= Cat.all.length %> cats tracked</h5>
      </div>

      <%= form_tag colonies_path, method: :get do %>
        <div class="d-flex align-items-center">
          <%= text_field_tag :query, params[:query], placeholder: "Enter an address", class: "form-control mr-2" %>
          <%= submit_tag "Find a colony", class: "btn btn-danger m-0" %>
        </div>
      <% end%>
      <a href="#tnr">Learn more</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div id="tnr">
  <div class="tnr-description">
    <h2 class="text-center" style="background-color: #448789; height: 60px;"><!-- <i class="fas fa-angle-down" style="color: white; margin-top: 15px;"></i> --></h2>

    <h2 class="text-center mb-4" style="padding-top: 130px;">What is TNR?</h2>
    <div class="container text-center mt-3" style= "width: 700px; padding-bottom: 100px;">
      <h5> Trap-Neuter-Return, or "TNR," is the most humane and effective method known for managing feral and stray cats and reducing their numbers. </h5>
    </div>
    <h2 class="text-center mb-5">The Process</h2>
  </div>

  <div data-aos="fade-up"
  data-aos-offset="200"
  data-aos-delay="50"
  data-aos-duration="1000"
  >

  <div class="tnr-cards d-flex flex-wrap align-items-center justify-content-around">
    <div class="card tnr-card shadow" style="padding: 50px; width: 300px; height: 400px; border-radius: 10px;">
      <h2 class="text-center pb-2" style="border-bottom: solid 2px;">Trap</h2>
      <p style="padding-top: 10px; text-align: justify;">
      The cats, who typically live together in a group called a colony, are trapped and brought to a veterinary clinic.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card tnr-card shadow" style="padding: 50px; width: 300px; height: 400px; border-radius: 10px;">
      <h2 class="text-center pb-2" style="border-bottom: solid 2px;">Neuter</h2>
      <p style="padding-top: 10px; text-align: justify;">They're then spayed or neutered, vaccinated for rabies where appropriate and eartipped. </p>
    </div>
    <div class="card tnr-card shadow" style="padding: 50px; width: 300px; height: 400px; border-radius: 10px;">
      <h2 class="text-center pb-2" style="border-bottom: solid 2px;">Release</h2>
      <p style="padding-top: 10px; text-align: justify;">After they've recovered from their surgeries, the cats are returned back to their original territory where a caretaker provides regular food and shelter.</p>
    </div>
    </div>
    <div class= "content" style="padding-top: 100px;">
        <h4 class="text-center">Make a difference today.</h4>
    </div>
  <div class="space-bottom d-flex justify-content-center mb-4" style="padding-bottom: 100px;">

    <%= link_to 'Create a colony', new_colony_path, class: "btn btn-success btn-round my-3" %>
  </div>
</div>
